{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778465519911,"sessionID":"ses_1eb31eb3fffedIiNDN7onOFnKg","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"chatcmpl-tool-9a9d3f7c9028519e","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/__issue_context__.json"},"output":"<path>/home/runner/work/eval-ont-agent-go/eval-ont-agent-go/__issue_context__.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"body\": \"\\nhttps://github.com/geneontology/go-ontology/issues/31038\\n\\nPlease provide as much information as you can:\\n\\n* **GO term ID and Label**\\n\\n* **Reason for deprecation** Put an x in the appropriate box: \\n \\n\\n - [ ]  The reason for obsoletion is that this term was added in error.\\n\\n* **\\\"Replace by\\\" term (ID and label)**\\n\\ncargo receptor activity (GO:0038024)\\n\\n\\n* **Are there annotations to this term?**\\n- How many EXP: 0\\n\\n\\n* **Any other information**\\nApologies, I  requested recently but think we should obsolete this.\\nWe can just use \\\"cargo receptor\\\" or one of the other children, like \\\"COPII receptor\\\"\\nThis term is problematic because most of the vesicle cargo are glycoproteins giving an additional axis of classification.\\nWe should organize by transport domains (i.e which vesicles they connect cargo to) rather than by substrate type (substrates can be captured by has_input)\\n\\n\\n\\n----\\nChecklist for ontology editor\\n\\n***Check term usage and metadata in Protégé***\\n- [ ] check term usage in the ontology \\n- [ ] check internal mappings: RHEA, EC, MetaCyc\\n- [ ] check subset usage\\n- [ ] check taxon constraints \\n\\n***Check annotations***\\n- [ ] create Annotation Review spreadsheet \\n- * Annotation Review template: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1izV3q1jnq_Ybg5MJ53O_b5BCTkGtjl_Fi-cOg3-7eBE/edit#gid=0\\n- * Instructions: https://wiki.geneontology.org/Annotation_Review_Request\\n- [ ] create annotation review ticket: https://github.com/geneontology/g